C++ programs have the file extension .cpp 

  

The terminal is the black panel to code on 

  

int main() is used to start a program 

  

#include <iostream> is a library  

  

std::cout is the "character output stream" 

  

<< is an operator used next to cout 

  

Use ";" to tell the computer you are at the end of a statement 

  

\n is used to start a new line 

Example: 

std::cout<<"Hello World!\n"; 
